title: Handy Brew Clever Dripper Set
description: The Clever coffee dripper combines the beauty of French Press and filter drip brewing, eliminating the drawbacks of each. Designed with a stopper in a detachable base of the dripper, you can control the steeping time with a sediment-free cup. The stopper keeps the coffee inside the dripper until you place it on a cup or decanter to lift up the stopper and drain your brew. Inclusive of 100 filters.

title: Kalita Wave Filter
description: The Kalita Wave filters pair with the Kalita Wave drippers to give a clean and consistent cup. Due to the wave ridges, the air pockets between the filter and the dripper help to enhance temperature stability by reducing water contact with the outer wall of the dripper. The white (bleached) ones have less of a paper taste than the brown (unbleached) Wave filters, but do not hold its shape as well as the brown (unbleached) ones as the white paper is thinner and needs more delicate handling.

title: MHW-3BOMBER Coffee Scale 2.0
description: We have tried many scales and came across these MHW-3BOMBER weigh scales that stands out for its minimalist design, features and affordability. With the ability to weigh in 0.1g increments, all the way up to 2kg, it is perfect for weighing and brewing coffees, for both espresso or filter coffees alike. A weighing scale that will greatly improve the consistency and accuracy of your brews.

title: Cafec Abaca Flat Bottom Filter Paper
description: CAFEC is the brain child of Sanyo Sangyo, the Japanese pioneer filter paper manufacturer which developed the world’s first cone shaped filter paper. The company is very passionate about coffee & specifically drip coffee and even have their own roastery and restaurant. They want to make drip coffee easily accessible to everyone, whether it is coffee professionals or home brewers. Over the years, they have brought about a host of innovations & industry firsts to their drip coffee equipment which includes ABACA filter paper & Arita ware coffee dripper.

title: Nylon x MiiR 12oz Flavour Cup
description: Part of our Go Green campaign is to encourage the use of reusable cups for those who need coffee on the go. We met with the guys from MiiR few years back at a coffee trade show in Boston and were impressed by their principles and mission to do better for the environment and communities. In line with our own philosophy to work closer with like-minded suppliers that produce a world class product whilst making a difference to our world, we are thrilled to be collaborating with MiiR for our latest coffee cup.

title: Kimberly-Clark Kimtech Precision Wipes
description: Kimtech Science Precision Wipes are value-conscious tissue wipers that offer reliable wiping performance for delicate tasks. They are 1-ply, compactly sized (4.4” x 8.4”), soft and absorbent, designed for general cleaning tasks and feature the anti-static (“anti-stat”) dispensing system. These versatile, value wipers useful for polishing glass, wiping surfaces, general cleaning tasks, including instrumentation, surface, parts and lens cleaning. The Pop-Up Box is coated to keep the wipes clean and dry and is designed for easy, one-at-a-time dispensing. We use it extensively to clean the lens of our refractometer after use!

title: Timemore B75 Crystal Eye Dripper
description: A relatively new dripper to the market, the Timemore B75 Dripper is a flat-bottom brewer designed for basket-style filters, like the Kalita wave filter paper. Its unique shape and wide base promotes faster drainage and ensures even extraction, delivering a cup with clarity, balanced flavours with plenty of sweetness from the coffee. This is the amber black version. Dimensions: 90 x 98 x 72mm Be sure to add some filter papers so you're ready to make some delicious brews immediately.

title: Espazzola Grouphead Cleaner v2.0
description: The latest version of Espazzola is a professional tool for cleaning the group-head of espresso machines. It is mounted into the group-head like a portafilter and uses the hot water from the machine for a thorough and comprehensive removal of the coffee residues from all surfaces. Instead of brushing the group-head by hand, the machine cleans itself almost automatically without scalding your hands. Fast, easy and safe!

title: Nylon x Kloth Tote Bag
description: The wait is over – introducing our brand-new Nylon Tote Bags! When we roll out new merchandise, it has always been our goal to simultaneously do good socially and environmentally. Over the years, we’ve had a few Nylon totes that tied in with our anniversaries. This year, we’ve partnered with Kloth Woman Up, an initiative empowering women in marginalized communities across Singapore and Malaysia. This group of industrious women are trained to operate machines to make pieces with their own hands. They can now earn extra income while creating beautiful pieces. Swipe to see the behind-the-scenes process! Available in two bold colors – yellow and blue – they perfectly echo the vibrancy of our coffee retail bags. Made from a blend of 65% recycled polyester and 35% organic cotton, there is a main compartment to carry everything you need and a handy front pocket to keep your essentials within easy reach. Get yours today and support women’s empowerment while looking good!

title: Timemore Wave Filter
description: We started using the Timemore flat bottom filter paper since 2024. This filter fits single cup flat bottom dripper including Timemore B75 crystal dripper, Kalita flat bottom drippers or the Origami dripper. These are made of natural wood fibers from Japan and do not contain any additives and is odourless. The wave design allows water to flow down evenly and the flat bottom helps with full contact of the water and the coffee grounds. The filters have a fine texture and better permeability that prevents fine particles from choking up the filter. Each pack of 50 filters are packaged in a box to hold the shape. This filter is suited for 1 cup brew.

title: Standart Issue 39
description: Awarded Best Coffee Magazine and Best European Indie Magazine of 2023, Standart is an independent print magazine that delves into the fascinating world of coffee culture, delivering inspiring literary journeys for coffee lovers, regardless of their level of expertise. Delivered quarterly to the doorsteps of more than 11,000 readers worldwide, each issue presents a harmonious blend of stories and perspectives encompassing every aspect of the coffee chain, from seed to cup. Covering a wide range of topics, from the historical to the sociological, scientific, and cultural, approaching every theme with precision and expertise.
